August 13, 1937.
George D. Chinn.

(1) Lexington Ave., west side, south from East 88th to 87th Streets, showing Immanuel Lutheran Church at the S.W. corner of the former, and a demolition, at the N.W. corner of the latter.

August 13, 1937.

George D. Chinn.

(2) 1290-98 Lexington Ave., at the N.W. corner of East 87th Street, showing a 5-story apartment house, the Columbia, under demoliti... This site, in conjunction with Nos. 133 to 125 East 87th Street (left) will be improved with a modern structure for the Consolidated Gas and Electric Co., as their Yorkville office.

August 13, 1937.

George D. Chinn.

(3) An extensive view northward on the west side of the Ave. and showing the new 2-story structure that will house the Yorkville office of the Consolidated Gas and Electric Co.
